	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Cape Town – Six prisoners have escaped from Pollsmoor prison in Tokai, Western Cape police said on Monday. Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Andre Traut said the inmates escaped around 23:25 on Sunday night. They apparently escaped from the youth and juvenile section of the prison, according to media reports. "Circumstances surrounding the incident are being investigated," he said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  